import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the x-coordinates of the points?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

```
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['x'], data['y'])
    ax.set_xlabel('X Coordinate')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y Coordinate')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between the x and y coordinates of the points?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Perform K-means clustering
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=3)
    kmeans.fit(data)
    labels = kmeans.predict(data)

    # Create scatter plot
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data.iloc[:, 0], data.iloc[:, 1], c=labels, cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel(data.columns[0])
    ax.set_ylabel(data.columns[1])
    ax.set_title('Are there any clusters or groups of points in the dataset?')

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
``` 

This code performs K-means clustering on the given dataset and creates a scatter plot with the clusters colored differently. The chart title is set to "Are there any clusters or groups of points in the dataset?". The x-axis and y-axis labels are set to the names of the first and second columns in the dataset, respectively. The chart is returned as a matplotlib object.
